The paper deals with distance oracle constructions for graphs, which is a topic in data structures (cs.DS) and computational geometry (cs.CG). The focus is on planar graphs and minor-excluded graphs, which are also relevant to graph theory (cs.GT) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). Finally, the paper discusses the space and time complexity of the constructions, which is a common theme in algorithms and complexity theory (cs.SI).
